                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine and careful.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red (vivid red, strong crimson)</seg>
                        <date>19th century (?)</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; names of the donors; 1st, 2nd, 6th,
                           7th, 13th and 14th line on the incipit page of Text I; two initial lines
                           of parts of Text II; a few lines of the beginning of the daily readings
                           and their sections in Text I; the words salām laki, sǝḥat läkä and their
                           abbreviations in Text II; elements of punctuation signs; elements of
                           Ethiopic numerals. 
 The names Walatta Mikāʾel (fol. 31va, 32vb,
                           71vb) and Walda ʾAbiyä ʾƎgzʾi (fol. 38vb) are written in strong
                           crimson.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">Hairlines extending horizontal elements
                        of the majority of letters and their derivations (e.g., መ አ
                        ነ).</handNote>
                  </handDesc>
